    Enclosing class:
    BitwiseSpliterator
    public static final class BitwiseSpliterator.Or
extends BitwiseSpliterator
    Implementation of BitwiseSpliterator used to stream the indices of bits that result in the live state after the OR operation, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel. Words are cached as they are encountered, so any modifications after iteration begins may not be included.

      • Or

        public Or​(BitSet set1,
          BitSet set2,
          int position,
          int end)
        Creates a BitwiseSpliterator.And that will cover indices of bits resulting in the live state within the specified starting and ending indices position and end after an OR operation..
        Parameters:
        set1 - The first BitSet that will be operated on against set2.
        set2 - The second BitSet that will be operated on against set1.
        position - (inclusive) the first index to include.
        end - (exclusive) the index after the last index to include.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if set1 or set2 are null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if position is greater than or equal to end, or the sizes of set1 and set2 differ.
